By the similarity of triangles $PQA$ and $QTS$, we have  \[\frac{PQ}{QT} = \frac{PA}{QS}.\]We know $PQ = \sqrt{1025}$, $PA = 20$, and $QT = PT - PQ = PT - \sqrt{1025}$.  Substituting, we get \[\frac{\sqrt{1025}}{PT - \sqrt{1025}} = \frac{20}{QS}.\]Solving for $QS$, we find \[QS = \frac{20(PT - \sqrt{1025})}{\sqrt{1025}}.\]Then \[QR = \sqrt{QT^2 + RT^2} = \sqrt{(PT - \sqrt{1025})^2 + RT^2}\]and \[RD = \sqrt{RT^2 + TD^2}.\]Since $RT = QS - QT = \frac{20(PT - \sqrt{1025})}{\sqrt{1025}} - (PT - \sqrt{1025})$, we can substitute to find $QR$ and $RD$. Finally, $QR - RD$ can be computed.

\begin{align*}
QR - RD &= \sqrt{(PT - \sqrt{1025})^2 + RT^2} - \sqrt{RT^2 + TD^2} \\
&= \sqrt{(PT - \sqrt{1025})^2 + \left(\frac{20(PT - \sqrt{1025})}{\sqrt{1025}} - (PT - \sqrt{1025})\right)^2} - \sqrt{\left(\frac{20(PT - \sqrt{1025})}{\sqrt{1025}} - (PT - \sqrt{1025})\right)^2 + TD^2}.
\end{align*}

The value of $QR - RD$ will depend on the value of $PT$.

